text: Anna-Lena Löfgren, born 1 May 1944, dead 21 May 2010, was a singer from Stockholm, Sweden. Between 1962 and 1995, she scored more than 40 Svensktoppen hit songs. During the 1960s, she also scored successes in the German-speaking world. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:1944 births Category:2010 deaths Category:Singers from Stockholm
